#. type: Title ====
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:581
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pw`"
msgstr "`pw`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:586
msgid ""
"The man:pw[8] utility can create, remove, modify, and display users and groups.  "
"It functions as a front end to the system user and group files.  man:pw[8] has a "
"very powerful set of command line options that make it suitable for use in shell "
"scripts, but new users may find it more complicated than the other commands "
"presented in this section."
msgstr ""
"man:pw[8] 工具可以创建、删除、修改和显示用户和组。man:pw[8] 有一组非常强大的命令"
"行选项，使它适合于在 shell 脚本中使用，但新用户可能会发现它比本节介绍的其他命令更"
"复杂。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:588
#, no-wrap
msgid "Managing Groups"
msgstr "用户组管理"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:593
msgid ""
"A group is a list of users. A group is identified by its group name and GID.  In "
"FreeBSD, the kernel uses the UID of a process, and the list of groups it belongs "
"to, to determine what the process is allowed to do.  Most of the time, the GID "
"of a user or process usually means the first group in the list."
msgstr ""
"用户组是一个用户的列表。用户组由其组名和 GID 来识别。在 FreeBSD 中，内核使用一个进"
"程的 UID 和它所属的组的列表来决定这个进程被允许做什么。大多数时候，一个用户或进程"
"的 GID 通常意味着列表中的第一个组。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:598
msgid ""
"The group name to GID mapping is listed in [.filename]#/etc/group#.  This is a "
"plain text file with four colon-delimited fields.  The first field is the group "
"name, the second is the encrypted password, the third the GID, and the fourth "
"the comma-delimited list of members.  For a more complete description of the "
"syntax, refer to man:group[5]."
msgstr ""
"组名到 GID 的映射被列在 [.filename]#/etc/group# 中。这是一个纯文本文件，有四个以冒"
"号分隔的字段。第一个字段是组名，第二个是加密的密码，第三个是 GID ，第四个是以逗号"
"分隔的成员列表。关于语法的更完整描述，请参考 man:group[5] 。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:602
msgid ""
"The superuser can modify [.filename]#/etc/group# using a text editor.  "
"Alternatively, man:pw[8] can be used to add and edit groups.  For example, to "
"add a group called `teamtwo` and then confirm that it exists:"
msgstr ""
"超级用户可以使用文本编辑器修改 [.filename]#/etc/group# 。另外，可以用 man:pw[8] "
"来添加和编辑组。例如，添加一个名为 `teamtwo` 的组，然后确认它的存在："

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:603
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding a Group Using man:pw[8]"
msgstr "使用 man:pw[8] 添加一个组"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:611
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# pw groupadd teamtwo\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:\n"
msgstr ""
"# pw groupadd teamtwo\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:617
msgid ""
"In this example, `1100` is the GID of `teamtwo`.  Right now, `teamtwo` has no "
"members.  This command will add `jru` as a member of `teamtwo`."
msgstr ""
"在这个例子中， `1100` 是 `teamtwo` 的 GID。现在， `teamtwo` 没有成员。这个命令将"
"添加 `jru` 为 `teamtwo` 的成员。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:618
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding User Accounts to a New Group Using man:pw[8]"
msgstr "使用 man:pw[8] 将用户账户添加到一个新组中"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:626
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# pw groupmod teamtwo -M jru\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:jru\n"
msgstr ""
"# pw groupmod teamtwo -M jru\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:jru\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:633
msgid ""
"The argument to `-M` is a comma-delimited list of users to be added to a new "
"(empty) group or to replace the members of an existing group.  To the user, this "
"group membership is different from (and in addition to) the user's primary group "
"listed in the password file.  This means that the user will not show up as a "
"member when using `groupshow` with man:pw[8], but will show up when the "
"information is queried via man:id[1] or a similar tool.  When man:pw[8] is used "
"to add a user to a group, it only manipulates [.filename]#/etc/group# and does "
"not attempt to read additional data from [.filename]#/etc/passwd#."
msgstr ""
"`-M` 的参数是一个以逗号分隔的用户列表，用来添加到一个新的（空的）组或替换现有组的"
"成员。对用户来说，这个组的成员资格与密码文件中列出的用户的主组不同（而且是附加"
"的）。这意味着在使用 man:pw[8] 的 `groupshow` 时，用户不会显示为成员，但在通过 "
"man:id[1] 或类似工具查询信息时，会显示出来。当 man:pw[8] 被用来将一个用户添加到一"
"个组时，它只操作 [.filename]#/etc/group#  ，而不试图从 [.filename]#/etc/passwd#  "
"读取其他数据。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:634
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adding a New Member to a Group Using man:pw[8]"
msgstr "使用 man:pw[8] 向一个组添加新成员"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:642
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# pw groupmod teamtwo -m db\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:jru,db\n"
msgstr ""
"# pw groupmod teamtwo -m db\n"
"# pw groupshow teamtwo\n"
"teamtwo:*:1100:jru,db\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:647
msgid ""
"In this example, the argument to `-m` is a comma-delimited list of users who are "
"to be added to the group.  Unlike the previous example, these users are appended "
"to the group and do not replace existing users in the group."
msgstr ""
"在这个例子中， `-m` 的参数是一个以逗号分隔的用户列表，这些用户将被添加到该组。与"
"前面的例子不同，这些用户被添加到组中，并不取代组中的现有用户。"

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:648
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using man:id[1] to Determine Group Membership"
msgstr "使用 man:id[1] 来确定群组成员资格"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:655
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% id jru\n"
"uid=1001(jru) gid=1001(jru) groups=1001(jru), 1100(teamtwo)\n"
msgstr ""
"% id jru\n"
"uid=1001(jru) gid=1001(jru) groups=1001(jru), 1100(teamtwo)\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:659
msgid "In this example, `jru` is a member of the groups `jru` and `teamtwo`."
msgstr "在这个例子中， `jru` 是 `jru` 和 `teamtwo` 组的成员。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:661
msgid ""
