#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:833
#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD File Flags"
msgstr "FreeBSD 的文件标志"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:838
msgid ""
"In addition to file permissions, FreeBSD supports the use of \"file flags\".  "
"These flags add an additional level of security and control over files, but not "
"directories.  With file flags, even `root` can be prevented from removing or "
"altering files."
msgstr ""
"除了文件权限之外，FreeBSD 还支持使用“文件标志”。这些标志为文件，但不是目录，增加"
"了额外的安全和控制水平。通过文件标志，甚至可以阻止 root 删除或更改文件。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:841
msgid ""
"File flags are modified using man:chflags[1].  For example, to enable the system "
"undeletable flag on the file [.filename]#file1#, issue the following command:"
msgstr ""
"文件标志是用 man:chflags[1] 修改的。例如，要在文件 [.filename]#file1# 上启用系统"
"不可删除的标志，发出以下命令："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:845
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chflags sunlink file1\n"
msgstr "# chflags sunlink file1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:848
msgid ""
"To disable the system undeletable flag, put a \"no\" in front of the `sunlink`:"
msgstr "要禁用系统不可删除标志，请在 `sunlink` 前面加一个 \"no\"："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:852
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chflags nosunlink file1\n"
msgstr "# chflags nosunlink file1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:855
msgid "To view the flags of a file, use `-lo` with man:ls[1]:"
msgstr "要查看一个文件的标志，可以使用 man:ls[1] 中的 `-lo` ："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:859
#, no-wrap
msgid "# ls -lo file1\n"
msgstr "# ls -lo file1\n"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:864
#, no-wrap
msgid "-rw-r--r--  1 trhodes  trhodes  sunlnk 0 Mar  1 05:54 file1\n"
msgstr "-rw-r--r--  1 trhodes  trhodes  sunlnk 0 Mar  1 05:54 file1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:869
msgid ""
"Several file flags may only be added or removed by the `root` user.  In other "
"cases, the file owner may set its file flags.  Refer to man:chflags[1] and man:"
"chflags[2] for more information."
msgstr ""
"一些文件标志只能由 `root` 用户添加或删除。在其他情况下，文件所有者可以设置其文件"
"标志。更多信息请参考 man:chflags[1] 和 man:chflags[2]。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:870
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `setuid`, `setgid`, and `sticky` Permissions"
msgstr "`setuid`、 `setgid`  和 `sticky` 权限"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:874
msgid ""
"Other than the permissions already discussed, there are three other specific "
"settings that all administrators should know about.  They are the `setuid`, "
"`setgid`, and `sticky` permissions."
msgstr ""
"除了已经讨论过的权限之外，所有管理员都应该知道还有三个特定的设置：它们是 "
"`setuid`、 `setgid` 和 `sticky` 权限。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:877
msgid ""
"These settings are important for some UNIX(R) operations as they provide "
"functionality not normally granted to normal users.  To understand them, the "
"difference between the real user ID and effective user ID must be noted."
msgstr ""
"这些设置对某些 UNIX(R) 操作很重要，因为它们提供了通常不授予普通用户的功能。为了理"
"解它们，必须注意真实用户 ID 和有效用户 ID 之间的区别。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:883
msgid ""
"The real user ID is the UID who owns or starts the process.  The effective UID "
"is the user ID the process runs as.  As an example, man:passwd[1] runs with the "
"real user ID when a user changes their password.  However, in order to update "
"the password database, the command runs as the effective ID of the `root` user.  "
"This allows users to change their passwords without seeing a `Permission Denied` "
"error."
msgstr ""
"真正的用户 ID 是拥有或启动该进程的 UID。有效 UID 是进程运行的用户 ID 。举个例子，"
"当用户修改密码时， man:passwd[1] 以真实用户 ID 运行。然而，为了更新密码数据库，该"
"命令以根用户的有效 ID 运行。这使得用户在修改密码时不会看到“拒绝许可”的错误。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:885
msgid ""
"The setuid permission may be set by prefixing a permission set with the number "
"four (4) as shown in the following example:"
msgstr "setuid 权限可以通过在权限集前加上数字四(4)来设置，如下例所示："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:889
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod 4755 suidexample.sh\n"
msgstr "# chmod 4755 suidexample.sh\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:892
msgid "The permissions on [.filename]#suidexample.sh# now look like the following:"
msgstr "[.filename]#suidexample.sh# 的权限现在看起来如下："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:896
#, no-wrap
msgid "-rwsr-xr-x   1 trhodes  trhodes    63 Aug 29 06:36 suidexample.sh\n"
msgstr "-rwsr-xr-x   1 trhodes  trhodes    63 Aug 29 06:36 suidexample.sh\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:900
msgid ""
"Note that a `s` is now part of the permission set designated for the file owner, "
"replacing the executable bit.  This allows utilities which need elevated "
"permissions, such as man:passwd[1]."
msgstr ""
"请注意， `s`  现在是为文件所有者指定的权限集的一部分，取代了可执行位。他允许实用"
"程序提高权限，如 man:passwd[1] 。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:905
msgid ""
"The `nosuid` man:mount[8] option will cause such binaries to silently fail "
"without alerting the user.  That option is not completely reliable as a `nosuid` "
"wrapper may be able to circumvent it."
msgstr ""
"`nosuid` man:mount[8] 选项将导致这种二进制文件默默地失败而不提醒用户。这个选项并"
"不完全可靠，因为 `nosuid` 包装器可能会规避它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:910
msgid ""
"To view this in real time, open two terminals.  On one, type `passwd` as a "
"normal user.  While it waits for a new password, check the process table and "
"look at the user information for man:passwd[1]:"
msgstr ""
"要实时查看这个，请打开两个终端。在一个终端上，以普通用户的身份输入 `passwd` 。在"
"它等待新密码的时候，检查进程表并查看 man:passwd[1] 的用户信息："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:912
msgid "In terminal A:"
msgstr "在终端A："

