#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:917
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Changing local password for trhodes\n"
"Old Password:\n"
msgstr ""
"Changing local password for trhodes\n"
"Old Password:\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:920
msgid "In terminal B:"
msgstr "在终端B："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:924
#, no-wrap
msgid "# ps aux | grep passwd\n"
msgstr "# ps aux | grep passwd\n"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:930
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"trhodes  5232  0.0  0.2  3420  1608   0  R+    2:10AM   0:00.00 grep passwd\n"
"root     5211  0.0  0.2  3620  1724   2  I+    2:09AM   0:00.01 passwd\n"
msgstr ""
"trhodes  5232  0.0  0.2  3420  1608   0  R+    2:10AM   0:00.00 grep passwd\n"
"root     5211  0.0  0.2  3620  1724   2  I+    2:09AM   0:00.01 passwd\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:933
msgid ""
"Although man:passwd[1] is run as a normal user, it is using the effective UID of "
"`root`."
msgstr ""
"尽管 man:passwd[1] 是以普通用户的身份运行的，但它使用的是有效 UID，即 `root` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:936
msgid ""
"The `setgid` permission performs the same function as the `setuid` permission; "
"except that it alters the group settings.  When an application or utility "
"executes with this setting, it will be granted the permissions based on the "
"group that owns the file, not the user who started the process."
msgstr ""
"`setgid` 权限的功能与  `setuid` 权限的功能相同；只是它改变了组的设置。当一个应用"
"程序或实用程序以这种设置执行时，它将被授予基于拥有文件的组的权限，而不是启动该进"
"程的用户。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:938
msgid ""
"To set the `setgid` permission on a file, provide man:chmod[1] with a leading "
"two (2):"
msgstr "要在一个文件上设置 `setgid` 权限，请为 man:chmod[1] 提供前导 two(2)："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:942
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod 2755 sgidexample.sh\n"
msgstr "# chmod 2755 sgidexample.sh\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:945
msgid ""
"In the following listing, notice that the `s` is now in the field designated for "
"the group permission settings:"
msgstr "在下面的列表中，注意到 `s` 现在是在指定给组权限设置的区域："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:949
#, no-wrap
msgid "-rwxr-sr-x   1 trhodes  trhodes    44 Aug 31 01:49 sgidexample.sh\n"
msgstr "-rwxr-sr-x   1 trhodes  trhodes    44 Aug 31 01:49 sgidexample.sh\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:955
msgid ""
"In these examples, even though the shell script in question is an executable "
"file, it will not run with a different EUID or effective user ID.  This is "
"because shell scripts may not access the man:setuid[2] system calls."
msgstr ""
"在这些例子中，即使有关的 shell 脚本是一个可执行文件，它也不会以不同的 EUID 或有效"
"用户 ID 运行。这是因为 shell 脚本不能访问 man:setuid[2] 系统调用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:959
msgid ""
"The `setuid` and `setgid` permission bits may lower system security, by allowing "
"for elevated permissions.  The third special permission, the `sticky bit`, can "
"strengthen the security of a system."
msgstr ""
"`setuid` 和 `setgid` 权限位可能会降低系统的安全性，因为允许提升权限。第三个特殊权"
"限，`粘性位`，可以加强系统的安全性。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:963
msgid ""
"When the `sticky bit` is set on a directory, it allows file deletion only by the "
"file owner.  This is useful to prevent file deletion in public directories, such "
"as [.filename]#/tmp#, by users who do not own the file.  To utilize this "
"permission, prefix the permission set with a one (1):"
msgstr ""
"当一个目录上的`粘性位`被设置时，它只允许文件所有者删除文件。这对于防止不拥有文件"
"的用户在公共目录（如 [.filename]#/tmp# ）中删除文件很有用。要利用这个权限，请在权"
"限设置前加一个 1（1） ："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:967
#, no-wrap
msgid "# chmod 1777 /tmp\n"
msgstr "# chmod 1777 /tmp\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:970
msgid ""
"The `sticky bit` permission will display as a `t` at the very end of the "
"permission set:"
msgstr "`粘性位`权限将在权限集的最末端显示为 `t` ："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:974
#, no-wrap
msgid "# ls -al / | grep tmp\n"
msgstr "# ls -al / | grep tmp\n"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:979
#, no-wrap
msgid "drwxrwxrwt  10 root  wheel         512 Aug 31 01:49 tmp\n"
msgstr "drwxrwxrwt  10 root  wheel         512 Aug 31 01:49 tmp\n"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:982
#, no-wrap
msgid "Directory Structure"
msgstr "目录结构"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:988
msgid ""
"The FreeBSD directory hierarchy is fundamental to obtaining an overall "
"understanding of the system.  The most important directory is root or, \"/\".  "
"This directory is the first one mounted at boot time and it contains the base "
"system necessary to prepare the operating system for multi-user operation.  The "
"root directory also contains mount points for other file systems that are "
"mounted during the transition to multi-user operation."
msgstr ""
"了解 FreeBSD 的目录层次结构是理解系统整体的基础。最重要的目录是 root 或 \"/\" 。"
"这个目录是启动时挂载的第一个目录，它包含了为多用户操作准备的基本系统。根目录还包"
"含其他文件系统的挂载点，这些文件系统在过渡到多用户操作时被挂载。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:996
msgid ""
"A mount point is a directory where additional file systems can be grafted onto a "
"parent file system (usually the root file system).  This is further described in "
"<<disk-organization>>.  Standard mount points include [.filename]#/usr/#, [."
"filename]#/var/#, [.filename]#/tmp/#, [.filename]#/mnt/#, and [.filename]#/cdrom/"
"#.  These directories are usually referenced to entries in [.filename]#/etc/"
"fstab#.  This file is a table of various file systems and mount points and is "
"read by the system.  Most of the file systems in [.filename]#/etc/fstab# are "
"mounted automatically at boot time from the script man:rc[8] unless their entry "
"includes `noauto`.  Details can be found in <<disks-fstab>>."
msgstr ""
"挂载点是一个目录，其他文件系统可以嫁接到一个父文件系统（通常是根文件系统）上。这"
"将在<<磁盘组织>>中进一步描述。标准挂载点包括 [.filename]#/usr/#, [.filename]#/var/#,"
" [.filename]#/tmp/#, [.filename]#/mnt/# 和 [.filename]#/cdrom/# 。这些目录"
"通常被引用到 [.filename]#/etc/fstab# 中的条目。这个文件是各种文件系统和挂载点的表"
"格，由系统读取。 [.filename]#/etc/fstab# 中的大多数文件系统都是在启动时由脚本 "
"man:rc[8] 自动挂载的，除非它们的条目包含 `noauto` 。详细内容可以在 <<fstab 文件>> "
"中找到。"

