#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1304
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mounting and Unmounting File Systems"
msgstr "文件系统的挂载与卸载"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1307
msgid ""
"The file system is best visualized as a tree, rooted, as it were, at [."
"filename]#/#. [.filename]#/dev#, [.filename]#/usr#, and the other directories in "
"the root directory are branches, which may have their own branches, such as [."
"filename]#/usr/local#, and so on."
msgstr ""
"最好把文件系统看作是一棵树，它的根在 [.filename]#/#. [.filename]#/dev#,"
" [.filename]#/usr# 和根目录中的其他目录是分支，它们可能有自己的分支，如"
" [.filename]#/usr/local# 等等。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1311
msgid ""
"There are various reasons to house some of these directories on separate file "
"systems.  [.filename]#/var# contains the directories [.filename]#log/#, [."
"filename]#spool/#, and various types of temporary files, and as such, may get "
"filled up.  Filling up the root file system is not a good idea, so splitting [."
"filename]#/var# from [.filename]#/# is often favorable."
msgstr ""
"将这些目录中的一部分放在单独的文件系统中是有各种原因的。 [.filename]#/var# 包含"
"了 [.filename]#log/#, [.filename]#spool/# 和各种类型的临时文件，因此，可能会被填"
"满。填满根文件系统并不是一个好主意，所以将 [.filename]#/var# 从 [.filename]#/# 中"
"分离出来通常是有好处的。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1313
msgid ""
"Another common reason to contain certain directory trees on other file systems "
"is if they are to be housed on separate physical disks, or are separate virtual "
"disks, such as Network File System mounts, described in crossref:network-"
"servers[network-nfs,“Network File System (NFS)”], or CDROM drives."
msgstr ""
"在其他文件系统中包含某些目录树的另一个常见原因是，如果它们要被放置在单独的物理磁"
"盘上，或者是单独的虚拟磁盘，比如 crossref:network-servers[network-nfs,“网络文件系"
"统（NFS）”]中描述的网络文件系统挂载，或者 CDROM 驱动器。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1315
#, no-wrap
msgid "The [.filename]#fstab# File"
msgstr "[.filename]#fstab# 文件"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1319
msgid ""
"During the boot process (crossref:boot[boot,The FreeBSD Booting Process]), file "
"systems listed in [.filename]#/etc/fstab# are automatically mounted except for "
"the entries containing `noauto`.  This file contains entries in the following "
"format:"
msgstr ""
"在启动过程中（crossref:boot[boot,FreeBSD 的启动过程]），除了包含 `noauto` 的条目"
"外， [.filename]#/etc/fstab# 中列出的文件系统会自动挂载。这个文件包含以下格式的条"
"目："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1323
#, no-wrap
msgid "device       /mount-point fstype     options      dumpfreq     passno\n"
msgstr "device       /mount-point fstype     options      dumpfreq     passno\n"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1325
#, no-wrap
msgid "`device`"
msgstr "`device`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1327
msgid "An existing device name as explained in <<disks-naming>>."
msgstr "一个现有的设备名称，如磁盘设备名称中所解释的。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1328
#, no-wrap
msgid "`mount-point`"
msgstr "`mount-point`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1330
msgid "An existing directory on which to mount the file system."
msgstr "一个现有的目录，用来挂载文件系统。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1331
#, no-wrap
msgid "`fstype`"
msgstr "`fstype`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1334
msgid ""
"The file system type to pass to man:mount[8].  The default FreeBSD file system "
"is `ufs`."
msgstr "要传递给 man:mount[8] 的文件系统类型。FreeBSD 默认的文件系统是 `ufs`。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1335
#, no-wrap
msgid "`options`"
msgstr "`options`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1339
msgid ""
"Either `rw` for read-write file systems, or `ro` for read-only file systems, "
"followed by any other options that may be needed.  A common option is `noauto` "
"for file systems not normally mounted during the boot sequence.  Other options "
"are listed in man:mount[8]."
msgstr ""
"`rw` 表示读写文件系统， `ro` 表示只读文件系统，后面是可能需要的任何其他选项。一个"
"常见的选项是 `noauto`，用于在启动过程中一般不挂载的文件系统。其他选项在"
" man:mount[8] 中列出。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1340
#, no-wrap
msgid "`dumpfreq`"
msgstr "`dumpfreq`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1343
msgid ""
"Used by man:dump[8] to determine which file systems require dumping.  If the "
"field is missing, a value of zero is assumed."
msgstr ""
"被 man:dump[8] 用来确定哪些文件系统需要转储。如果该字段缺失，则假定其值为 0 。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1344
#, no-wrap
msgid "`passno`"
msgstr "`passno`"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1350
msgid ""
"Determines the order in which file systems should be checked.  File systems that "
"should be skipped should have their `passno` set to zero.  The root file system "
"needs to be checked before everything else and should have its `passno` set to "
"one.  The other file systems should be set to values greater than one.  If more "
"than one file system has the same `passno`, man:fsck[8] will attempt to check "
"file systems in parallel if possible."
msgstr ""
"决定文件系统应被检查的顺序。应该被跳过的文件系统应该把它们的 `passno` 设置为 0 。"
"根文件系统需要在其他所有文件系统之前被检查，它的 `passno` 应该被设置为 1 。其他文"
"件系统应该被设置为大于 1 的值。如果多个文件系统有相同的 `passno` ，man:fsck[8] "
"将尽可能地尝试并行检查文件系统。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1352
msgid ""
"Refer to man:fstab[5] for more information on the format of [.filename]#/etc/"
"fstab# and its options."
msgstr ""
"关于 [.filename]#/etc/fstab# 的格式和选项的更多信息，请参考 man:fstab[5] 。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1354
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using man:mount[8]"
msgstr "使用 man:mount[8]"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1358
msgid ""
"File systems are mounted using man:mount[8].  The most basic syntax is as "
"follows:"
msgstr "文件系统是用 man:mount[8] 挂载的。最基本的语法如下："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1364
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mount device mountpoint\n"
msgstr "# mount device mountpoint\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1368
msgid ""
"This command provides many options which are described in man:mount[8], The most "
"commonly used options include:"
msgstr "该命令提供了许多选项，在 man:mount[8] 中有所描述，最常用的选项包括："

#. type: Block title
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1369
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mount Options"
msgstr "安装选项"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1370
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-a`"
msgstr "`-a`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1372
msgid ""
"Mount all the file systems listed in [.filename]#/etc/fstab#, except those "
"marked as \"noauto\", excluded by the `-t` flag, or those that are already "
"mounted."
msgstr ""
"挂载 [.filename]#/etc/fstab# 中列出的所有文件系统，除了那些标记为 \"noauto\"、被 "
"`-t` 标志排除的文件系统，或者已经挂载的文件系统。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1373
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-d`"
msgstr "`-d`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1376
msgid ""
"Do everything except for the actual mount system call.  This option is useful in "
"conjunction with the `-v` flag to determine what man:mount[8] is actually trying "
"to do."
msgstr ""
"除了实际的 mount 系统调用，做所有的事情。这个选项和 `-v` 标志一起使用，可以确定 "
"man:mount[8] 实际上要做什么。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1377
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-f`"
msgstr "`-f`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1379
msgid ""
"Force the mount of an unclean file system (dangerous), or the revocation of "
"write access when downgrading a file system's mount status from read-write to "
"read-only."
msgstr ""
"强制不干净的文件系统挂载(危险)，或者在将文件系统的挂载状态从读写降级为只读时取消"
"写访问。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1380
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-r`"
msgstr "`-r`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1383
msgid "Mount the file system read-only.  This is identical to using `-o ro`."
msgstr "挂载文件系统为只读。这与使用 `-o ro` 是一样的。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1384
#, no-wrap
msgid "``-t _fstype_``"
msgstr "``-t _fstype_``"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1387
msgid ""
"Mount the specified file system type or mount only file systems of the given "
"type, if `-a` is included.  \"ufs\" is the default file system type."
msgstr ""
"挂载指定的文件系统类型或只挂载指定类型的文件系统，如果包括 `-a` 。 \"ufs\" 是默认"
"的文件系统类型。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1388
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-u`"
msgstr "`-u`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1390
msgid "Update mount options on the file system."
msgstr "更新文件系统的挂载选项。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1391
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-v`"
msgstr "`-v`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1393
msgid "Be verbose."
msgstr "详细模式。"

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1394
#, no-wrap
msgid "`-w`"
msgstr "`-w`"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1396
msgid "Mount the file system read-write."
msgstr "对文件系统进行读写挂载。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1398
msgid "The following options can be passed to `-o` as a comma-separated list:"
msgstr "以下选项可以作为逗号分隔的列表传递给 `-o` ："

#. type: Labeled list
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1399
#, no-wrap
msgid "nosuid"
msgstr "nosuid"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1402
msgid ""
"Do not interpret setuid or setgid flags on the file system.  This is also a "
"useful security option."
msgstr "不要读取文件系统上的 setuid 或 setgid 标志。这也是一个有用的安全选项。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1404
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using man:umount[8]"
msgstr "使用 man:umount[8]"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1408
msgid ""
"To unmount a file system use man:umount[8].  This command takes one parameter "
"which can be a mountpoint, device name, `-a` or `-A`."
msgstr ""
"要卸载一个文件系统，使用 man:umount[8]。这个命令需要一个参数，可以是挂载点、设备"
"名称、 `-a` 或 `-A` 。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1411
msgid ""
"All forms take `-f` to force unmounting, and `-v` for verbosity.  Be warned that "
"`-f` is not generally a good idea as it might crash the computer or damage data "
"on the file system."
msgstr ""
"所有的形式都是用 `-f` 来强制卸载，用 `-v` 来表示详细情况。请注意，`-f` 通常不是一"
"个好主意，因为它可能使计算机崩溃或损坏文件系统上的数据。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1414
msgid ""
"To unmount all mounted file systems, or just the file system types listed after "
"`-t`, use `-a` or `-A`. Note that `-A` does not attempt to unmount the root "
"file system."
msgstr ""
"要卸载所有挂载的文件系统，或只卸载 `-t`  后面列出的文件系统类型，请使用 `-a` "
"或  `-A` 。注意， `-A` 不会试图卸载根文件系统。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1416
#, no-wrap
msgid "Processes and Daemons"
msgstr "进程和守护进程"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1421
msgid ""
"FreeBSD is a multi-tasking operating system.  Each program running at any one "
"time is called a _process_.  Every running command starts at least one new "
"process and there are a number of system processes that are run by FreeBSD."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 是一个多任务的操作系统。在任何时候运行的每一个程序都被称为一个 _进程_ 。"
"每个正在运行的命令都会启动至少一个新的进程，并且有许多系统进程被 FreeBSD 所运行。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1427
msgid ""
"Each process is uniquely identified by a number called a _process ID_ (PID).  "
"Similar to files, each process has one owner and group, and the owner and group "
"permissions are used to determine which files and devices the process can open.  "
"Most processes also have a parent process that started them.  For example, the "
"shell is a process, and any command started in the shell is a process which has "
"the shell as its parent process.  The exception is a special process called man:"
"init[8] which is always the first process to start at boot time and which always "
"has a PID of `1`."
msgstr ""
"每个进程都由一个称为 _进程 ID_ （PID）的数字来唯一识别。与文件类似，每个进程都有"
"一个所有者和组，所有者和组的权限被用来决定进程可以打开哪些文件和设备。大多数进程"
"也有一个启动它们的父进程。例如，shell 是一个进程，在 shell 中启动的任何命令都是一"
"个以 shell 为父进程的进程。例外的是一个叫做 man:init[8] 的特殊进程，它总是在启动"
"时第一个启动的进程，它的 PID 总是为 `1` 。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1434
msgid ""
"Some programs are not designed to be run with continuous user input and "
"disconnect from the terminal at the first opportunity.  For example, a web "
"server responds to web requests, rather than user input.  Mail servers are "
"another example of this type of application.  These types of programs are known "
"as _daemons_.  The term daemon comes from Greek mythology and represents an "
"entity that is neither good nor evil, and which invisibly performs useful "
"tasks.  This is why the BSD mascot is the cheerful-looking daemon with sneakers "
"and a pitchfork."
msgstr ""
"有些程序的设计不是为了在用户连续输入的情况下运行，而是一有机会就断开与终端的连"
"接。例如，网络服务器响应的是网络请求，而不是用户输入。邮件服务器是这种类型的应用"
"程序的另一个例子。这些类型的程序被称为 _守护程序_ 。守护进程这一术语来自希腊神"
"话，代表了一个既非善也非恶的实体，它在无形中执行着有用的任务。这就是 BSD 的吉祥物"
"是一个穿着运动鞋、拿着干草叉、看起来很欢快的守护者的原因。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1440
msgid ""
"There is a convention to name programs that normally run as daemons with a "
"trailing \"d\".  For example, BIND is the Berkeley Internet Name Domain, but the "
"actual program that executes is `named`.  The Apache web server program is "
"`httpd` and the line printer spooling daemon is `lpd`.  This is only a naming "
"convention.  For example, the main mail daemon for the Sendmail application is "
"`sendmail`, and not `maild`."
msgstr ""
"有一个惯例是用尾部的 \"d\" 来命名那些通常作为守护程序运行的程序。例如，BIND 是伯"
"克利互联网名称域，但实际执行的程序被命名为 `named`。 Apache 网络服务器程序是 "
"`httpd`，行式打印机的 spoolingdaemon 是 `lpd`。这只是一个命名惯例。例如，"
"Sendmail 应用程序的主要邮件守护程序是 `sendmail`，而不是 `maild`。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1441
#, no-wrap
msgid "Viewing Processes"
msgstr "查看流程"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1446
msgid ""
"To see the processes running on the system, use man:ps[1] or man:top[1].  To "
"display a static list of the currently running processes, their PIDs, how much "
"memory they are using, and the command they were started with, use man:ps[1].  "
"To display all the running processes and update the display every few seconds in "
"order to interactively see what the computer is doing, use man:top[1]."
msgstr ""
"要查看系统中运行的进程，使用 man:ps[1] 或 man:top[1] 。要显示当前正在运行的进程的"
"静态列表、它们的 PID、它们正在使用多少内存以及它们是用什么命令启动的，使用"
" man:ps[1] 。要显示所有正在运行的进程并每隔几秒钟更新一次，以便交互式地查看计算机正在"
"做什么，使用 man:top[1]。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1449
msgid ""
"By default, man:ps[1] only shows the commands that are running and owned by the "
"user.  For example:"
msgstr "默认情况下， man:ps[1] 只显示正在运行并由用户拥有的命令。比如说："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% ps\n"
" PID TT  STAT    TIME COMMAND\n"
"8203  0  Ss   0:00.59 /bin/csh\n"
"8895  0  R+   0:00.00 ps\n"
msgstr ""
"% ps\n"
" PID TT  STAT    TIME COMMAND\n"
"8203  0  Ss   0:00.59 /bin/csh\n"
"8895  0  R+   0:00.00 ps\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1466
msgid ""
"The output from man:ps[1] is organized into a number of columns.  The `PID` "
"column displays the process ID.  PIDs are assigned starting at 1, go up to "
"99999, then wrap around back to the beginning.  However, a PID is not reassigned "
"if it is already in use.  The `TT` column shows the tty the program is running "
"on and `STAT` shows the program's state.  `TIME` is the amount of time the "
"program has been running on the CPU.  This is usually not the elapsed time since "
"the program was started, as most programs spend a lot of time waiting for things "
"to happen before they need to spend time on the CPU.  Finally, `COMMAND` is the "
"command that was used to start the program."
msgstr ""
"man:ps[1] 的输出被组织成若干列。`PID` 列显示进程的 ID 。PID 从  1  开始分配，一直"
"到 99999 ，然后再绕回开头。然而，如果一个 PID 已经被使用，则不会被重新分配。 "
"`TT` 列显示了程序正在运行的 tty ， `STAT` 显示了程序的状态。`TIME` 是该程序在 "
"CPU 上运行的时间。这通常不是程序启动后所经过的时间，因为大多数程序在需要在 CPU 上"
"花费时间之前，会花很多时间来等待事情的发生。最后，`COMMAND` 是用来启动程序的命"
"令。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1469
msgid ""
"A number of different options are available to change the information that is "
"displayed.  One of the most useful sets is `auxww`, where `a` displays "
"information about all the running processes of all users, `u` displays the "
"username and memory usage of the process' owner, `x` displays information about "
"daemon processes, and `ww` causes man:ps[1] to display the full command line for "
"each process, rather than truncating it once it gets too long to fit on the "
"screen."
msgstr ""
"有许多不同的选项可以改变所显示的信息。其中最有用的一组是 `auxww`， `a` 显示所"
"有用户的所有运行进程的信息， `u` 显示进程所有者的用户名和内存使用情况， `x` 显示"
"守护进程的信息， `ww` 使 man:ps[1] 显示每个进程的完整命令行，而不是在它太长而无"
"法在屏幕上显示时截断它。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1471
msgid "The output from man:top[1] is similar:"
msgstr "man:top[1] 的输出也类似："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% top\n"
"last pid:  9609;  load averages:  0.56,  0.45,  0.36              up 0+00:20:03  10:21:46\n"
"107 processes: 2 running, 104 sleeping, 1 zombie\n"
"CPU:  6.2% user,  0.1% nice,  8.2% system,  0.4% interrupt, 85.1% idle\n"
"Mem: 541M Active, 450M Inact, 1333M Wired, 4064K Cache, 1498M Free\n"
"ARC: 992M Total, 377M MFU, 589M MRU, 250K Anon, 5280K Header, 21M Other\n"
"Swap: 2048M Total, 2048M Free\n"
msgstr ""
"% top\n"
"last pid:  9609;  load averages:  0.56,  0.45,  0.36              up 0+00:20:03  10:21:46\n"
"107 processes: 2 running, 104 sleeping, 1 zombie\n"
"CPU:  6.2% user,  0.1% nice,  8.2% system,  0.4% interrupt, 85.1% idle\n"
"Mem: 541M Active, 450M Inact, 1333M Wired, 4064K Cache, 1498M Free\n"
"ARC: 992M Total, 377M MFU, 589M MRU, 250K Anon, 5280K Header, 21M Other\n"
"Swap: 2048M Total, 2048M Free\n"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1494
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  PID USERNAME    THR PRI NICE   SIZE    RES STATE   C   TIME   WCPU COMMAND\n"
