"How to set an environment variable differs between shells.  In man:tcsh[1] and "
"man:csh[1], use `setenv` to set environment variables.  In man:sh[1] and `bash`, "
"use `export` to set the current environment variables.  This example sets the "
"default `EDITOR` to [.filename]#/usr/local/bin/emacs# for the man:tcsh[1] shell:"
msgstr ""
"不同的 shell 设置环境变量的方法也是不同的。在 man:tcsh[1] 和 man:csh[1] 中，使用 "
"`setenv` 来设置环境变量。在 man:sh[1] 和 `bash` 中，使用 `export` 来设置当前环境"
"变量。这个例子将 man:tcsh[1] shell 的默认 `EDITOR` 设置为"
" [.filename]#/usr/local/bin/emacs# ："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1664
#, no-wrap
msgid "% setenv EDITOR /usr/local/bin/emacs\n"
msgstr "% setenv EDITOR /usr/local/bin/emacs\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1667
msgid "The equivalent command for `bash` would be:"
msgstr "`bash` 的对应命令是："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1671
#, no-wrap
msgid "% export EDITOR=\"/usr/local/bin/emacs\"\n"
msgstr "% export EDITOR=\"/usr/local/bin/emacs\"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1675
msgid ""
"To expand an environment variable in order to see its current setting, type a `"
"$` character in front of its name on the command line.  For example, `echo "
"$TERM` displays the current `$TERM` setting."
msgstr ""
"要展开一个环境变量以查看其当前设置，请在命令行上的名称前输入 `$` 字符。例如， "
"`echo $TERM` 显示当前的 `$TERM` 设置。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1680
msgid ""
"Shells treat special characters, known as meta-characters, as special "
"representations of data.  The most common meta-character is `\\*`, which "
"represents any number of characters in a filename.  Meta-characters can be used "
"to perform filename globbing.  For example, `echo *` is equivalent to `ls` "
"because the shell takes all the files that match `*` and `echo` lists them on "
"the command line."
msgstr ""
"Shell 将特殊字符（称为元字符）视为数据的特殊代表。最常见的元字符是 `\\*` ，它代"
"表文件名中的任何数量的字符。元字符可以用来执行文件名正则化。例如，`echo *` 等同"
"于 `ls` ，因为 shell 将所有与 `*` 相匹配的文件拿出来， `echo` 将它们列在命令行"
"上。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1683
msgid ""
"To prevent the shell from interpreting a special character, escape it from the "
"shell by starting it with a backslash (`\\`).  For example, `echo $TERM` prints "
"the terminal setting whereas `echo \\$TERM` literally prints the string `$TERM`."
msgstr ""
"为了防止 shell 解释一个特殊的字符，可以用反斜杠（`\\`）开头来转义。例如， `echo "
"$TERM` 打印终端设置，而 `echo \\$TERM` 则是打印字符串 `$TERM`。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1685
#, no-wrap
msgid "Changing the Shell"
msgstr "改变 Shell"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1690
msgid ""
"The easiest way to permanently change the default shell is to use `chsh`.  "
"Running this command will open the editor that is configured in the `EDITOR` "
"environment variable, which by default is set to man:vi[1].  Change the `Shell:` "
"line to the full path of the new shell."
msgstr ""
"永久改变默认 shell 的最简单方法是使用 `chsh`。运行这个命令将打开在 `EDITOR` 环境"
"变量中配置的编辑器，默认情况下，它被设置为 man:vi[1] 。将 `Shell:` 一行改为新 "
"Shell 的完整路径。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1693
msgid ""
"Alternately, use `chsh -s` which will set the specified shell without opening an "
"editor.  For example, to change the shell to `bash`:"
msgstr ""
"另外，使用 `chsh -s` 可以在不打开编辑器的情况下设置指定的shell。例如，要把 "
"shell 改为 `bash`："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1697
#, no-wrap
msgid "% chsh -s /usr/local/bin/bash\n"
msgstr "% chsh -s /usr/local/bin/bash\n"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1704
msgid ""
"The new shell _must_ be present in [.filename]#/etc/shells#.  If the shell was "
"installed from the FreeBSD Ports Collection as described in crossref:ports[ports,"
"Installing Applications: Packages and Ports], it should be automatically added "
"to this file.  If it is missing, add it using this command, replacing the path "
"with the path of the shell:"
msgstr ""
"新的 shell 必须出现在 [.filename]#/etc/shells# 中。如果 shell 是从 FreeBSD Ports "
"Collection 安装的，如crossref:ports[ports,安装应用程序:包和端口]中所述，它应该自"
"动添加到这个文件中。如果没有，请用这个命令添加它，用 shell 的路径代替它的路径："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1708
#, no-wrap
msgid "# echo /usr/local/bin/bash >> /etc/shells\n"
msgstr "# echo /usr/local/bin/bash >> /etc/shells\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1711
msgid "Then, rerun man:chsh[1]."
msgstr "然后，重新运行 man:chsh[1] 。"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1713
#, no-wrap
msgid "Advanced Shell Techniques"
msgstr "高级 shell 技术"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1717
msgid ""
"The UNIX(R) shell is not just a command interpreter, it acts as a powerful tool "
"which allows users to execute commands, redirect their output, redirect their "
"input and chain commands together to improve the final command output.  When "
"this functionality is mixed with built in commands, the user is provided with an "
"environment that can maximize efficiency."
msgstr ""
"UNIX(R) shell 不仅仅是一个命令解释器，作为一个强大的工具，他允许用户执行命令，重"
"定向其输出，重定向其输入，并将命令连锁起来，以提高最终的命令输出。当这种功能与内"
"置的命令混合在一起时，就为用户提供了一个可以使效率最大化的环境。"

#. type: delimited block = 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1720
msgid ""
"Shell redirection is the action of sending the output or the input of a command "
"into another command or into a file.  To capture the output of the man:ls[1] "
"command, for example, into a file, redirect the output:"
msgstr ""
"Shell 重定向是将一条命令的输出或输入发送到另一条命令或文件中的行为。例如，要把 "
"man:ls[1] 命令的输出抓到一个文件中去，就要把输出重定向："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1724
#, no-wrap
msgid "% ls > directory_listing.txt\n"
msgstr "% ls > directory_listing.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1729
msgid ""
"The directory contents will now be listed in [.filename]#directory_listing."
"txt#.  Some commands can be used to read input, such as man:sort[1].  To sort "
"this listing, redirect the input:"
msgstr ""
"现在目录内容将被列在 [.filename]#directory_listing.txt# 中。有些命令可以用来读取"
"输入，比如 man:sort[1] 。要对这个列表进行排序，请重定向输入："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1733
#, no-wrap
msgid "% sort < directory_listing.txt\n"
msgstr "% sort < directory_listing.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1737
msgid ""
"The input will be sorted and placed on the screen.  To redirect that input into "
"another file, one could redirect the output of man:sort[1] by mixing the "
"direction:"
msgstr ""
"输入将被排序并放在屏幕上。为了将该输入重定向到另一个文件，可以通过混合方向来重定"
"向 man:sort[1] 的输出："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1741
#, no-wrap
msgid "% sort < directory_listing.txt > sorted.txt\n"
msgstr "% sort < directory_listing.txt > sorted.txt\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1749
msgid ""
"In all of the previous examples, the commands are performing redirection using "
"file descriptors.  Every UNIX(R) system has file descriptors, which include "
"standard input (stdin), standard output (stdout), and standard error (stderr).  "
"Each one has a purpose, where input could be a keyboard or a mouse, something "
"that provides input.  Output could be a screen or paper in a printer.  And error "
"would be anything that is used for diagnostic or error messages.  All three are "
"considered I/O based file descriptors and sometimes considered streams."
msgstr ""
"在前面所有的例子中，命令都是使用文件描述符进行重定向的。每个UNIX(R) 系统都有文件"
"描述符，包括标准输入（stdin）、标准输出（stdout）和标准错误（stderr）。每一个都有"
"一个目的，其中输入可以是键盘或鼠标，是提供输入的东西。输出可以是屏幕或打印机中的"
"纸张。而错误则是任何用于诊断或错误信息的东西。这三个都被认为是基于 I/O 的文件描述"
"符，有时也被认为是流。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1752
msgid ""
"Through the use of these descriptors, the shell allows output and input to be "
"passed around through various commands and redirected to or from a file.  "
"Another method of redirection is the pipe operator."
msgstr ""
"通过使用这些描述符，shell 允许输出和输入通过各种命令传递，并重定向到一个文件或从"
"一个文件输出。另一种重定向的方法是管道操作符。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1755
msgid ""
"The UNIX(R) pipe operator, \"|\" allows the output of one command to be directly "
"passed or directed to another program.  Basically, a pipe allows the standard "
"output of a command to be passed as standard input to another command, for "
"example:"
msgstr ""
"UNIX(R) 管道操作符 \"|\" 允许将一个命令的输出直接传递或引导到另一个程序。基本上，"
"管道允许将一个命令的标准输出作为标准输入传递给另一个命令，例如："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1759
#, no-wrap
msgid "% cat directory_listing.txt | sort | less\n"
msgstr "% cat directory_listing.txt | sort | less\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1763
msgid ""
"In that example, the contents of [.filename]#directory_listing.txt# will be "
"sorted and the output passed to man:less[1].  This allows the user to scroll "
"through the output at their own pace and prevent it from scrolling off the "
"screen."
msgstr ""
"在这个例子中， [.filename]#directory_listing.txt# 的内容将被排序，输出结果传递给 "
"man:less[1] 。这使得用户可以按照自己的节奏滚动浏览输出，并防止其滚出屏幕。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1765
#, no-wrap
msgid "Text Editors"
msgstr "文本编辑器"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1769
msgid ""
"Most FreeBSD configuration is done by editing text files, so it is a good idea "
"to become familiar with a text editor.  FreeBSD comes with a few as part of the "
"base system, and many more are available in the Ports Collection."
msgstr ""
"大多数 FreeBSD 的配置是通过编辑文本文件完成的，因此熟悉文本编辑器是一个好主意。"
"FreeBSD 的基本系统中自带了一些文本编辑器，而在 Ports Collection 中还有很多可选。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1776
msgid ""
"A simple editor to learn is man:ee[1], which stands for easy editor.  To start "
"this editor, type `ee _filename_` where _filename_ is the name of the file to be "
"edited.  Once inside the editor, all of the commands for manipulating the "
"editor's functions are listed at the top of the display.  The caret (`^`) "
"represents kbd:[Ctrl], so `^e` expands to kbd:[Ctrl+e].  To leave man:ee[1], "
"press kbd:[Esc], then choose the \"leave editor\" option from the main menu.  "
"The editor will prompt to save any changes if the file has been modified."
msgstr ""
"一个可以快速学习的，简单的编辑器是 man:ee[1]，它代表了 easyeditor 。要启动这个编"
"辑器，键入 `ee _filename_` ，其中 _filename_ 是要编辑的文件的名称。进入编辑器"
"后，所有用于操作编辑器功能的命令都列在显示屏的顶部。粗体字 （`^`） 代表 Ctrl ，所"
"以 `^e` 扩展为 kbd:[Ctrl+e] 。要离开 man:ee[1]，按 kbd:[Esc]，然后在主菜单中选"
"择 \"leave editor\" 选项。如果文件被修改了，编辑器会提示保存所有修改。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1781
msgid ""
"FreeBSD also comes with more powerful text editors, such as man:vi[1], as part "
"of the base system.  Other editors, like package:editors/emacs[] and package:"
"editors/vim[], are part of the FreeBSD Ports Collection.  These editors offer "
"more functionality at the expense of being more complicated to learn.  Learning "
"a more powerful editor such as vim or Emacs can save more time in the long run."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 还提供了更强大的文本编辑器，如 man:vi[1] ，作为基本系统的一部分。其他的编"
"辑器，像 package:editors/emacs[] 和 package:editors/vim[] ，是FreeBSD Ports "
"Collection 的一部分。这些编辑器提供了更多的功能，但代价是学习起来更加复杂。学习一"
"个更强大的编辑器，如 vim 或 Emacs ，从长远来看可以节省更多时间。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1784
msgid ""
"Many applications which modify files or require typed input will automatically "
"open a text editor.  To change the default editor, set the `EDITOR` environment "
"variable as described in <<shells>>."
msgstr ""
"许多修改文件或需要输入的应用程序会自动打开一个文本编辑器。要改变默认的编辑器，请"
"设置 `EDITOR` 环境变量，如 Shell 中所述。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1786
#, no-wrap
msgid "Devices and Device Nodes"
msgstr "设备和设备节点"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1791
msgid ""
"A device is a term used mostly for hardware-related activities in a system, "
"including disks, printers, graphics cards, and keyboards.  When FreeBSD boots, "
"the majority of the boot messages refer to devices being detected.  A copy of "
"the boot messages are saved to [.filename]#/var/run/dmesg.boot#."
msgstr ""
"设备是一个术语，主要用于系统中的硬件相关活动，包括磁盘、打印机、显卡和键盘。当 "
"FreeBSD 启动时，大部分的启动信息都是指正在检测的设备。开机信息的副本被保存在"
" [.filename]#/var/run/dmesg.boot# 中。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1794
msgid ""
"Each device has a device name and number.  For example, [.filename]#ada0# is the "
"first SATA hard drive, while [.filename]#kbd0# represents the keyboard."
msgstr ""
"每个设备都有一个设备名称和编号。例如， [.filename]#ada0# 是第一个 SATA 硬盘，而 "
"[.filename]#kbd0# 代表键盘。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1796
msgid ""
"Most devices in FreeBSD must be accessed through special files called device "
"nodes, which are located in [.filename]#/dev#."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 中的大多数设备必须通过特殊的文件访问，这些文件被称为设备节点，位于"
" [.filename]#/dev# 中。"

#. type: Title ==
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1798
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manual Pages"
msgstr "手册页"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1803
msgid ""
"The most comprehensive documentation on FreeBSD is in the form of manual pages.  "
"Nearly every program on the system comes with a short reference manual "
"explaining the basic operation and available arguments.  These manuals can be "
"viewed using `man`:"
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 上最全面的文档是以手册页的形式出现的。几乎系统中的每一个程序都有一个简短"
"的参考手册，解释其基本操作和可用参数。这些手册可以用 `man` 来查看："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1807
#, no-wrap
msgid "% man command\n"
msgstr "% man command\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1811
msgid ""
"where _command_ is the name of the command to learn about.  For example, to "
"learn more about man:ls[1], type:"
msgstr ""
"其中命令是要了解的命令的名称。例如，要了解更多关于 man:ls[1] 的信息，请输入："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1815
#, no-wrap
msgid "% man ls\n"
msgstr "% man ls\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1819
msgid ""
"Manual pages are divided into sections which represent the type of topic.  In "
"FreeBSD, the following sections are available:"
msgstr "手册页面被划分为代表主题类型的章节。在 FreeBSD 中，有以下几个部分："

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1821
msgid "User commands."
msgstr "用户指令。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1822
msgid "System calls and error numbers."
msgstr "系统调用和错误号码。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1823
msgid "Functions in the C libraries."
msgstr "C 库中的函数。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1824
msgid "Device drivers."
msgstr "设备驱动程序。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1825
msgid "File formats."
msgstr "文件格式。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1826
msgid "Games and other diversions."
msgstr "游戏和其他消遣活动。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1827
msgid "Miscellaneous information."
msgstr "杂项信息。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1828
msgid "System maintenance and operation commands."
msgstr "系统维护和操作命令。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1829
msgid "System kernel interfaces."
msgstr "系统内核接口。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1833
msgid ""
"In some cases, the same topic may appear in more than one section of the online "
"manual.  For example, there is a `chmod` user command and a `chmod()` system "
"call.  To tell man:man[1] which section to display, specify the section number:"
msgstr ""
"在某些情况下，同一个主题可能会出现在在线手册的多个部分。例如，有一个 `chmod` 用户"
"命令和一个 `chmod()` 系统调用。要告诉 man:man[1] 要显示哪一节，需要指定节号："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1837
#, no-wrap
msgid "% man 1 chmod\n"
msgstr "% man 1 chmod\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1841
msgid ""
"This will display the manual page for the user command man:chmod[1].  References "
"to a particular section of the online manual are traditionally placed in "
"parenthesis in written documentation, so man:chmod[1] refers to the user command "
"and man:chmod[2] refers to the system call."
msgstr ""
"这将显示用户命令 man:chmod[1] 的手册页面。在书面文档中，对在线手册特定章节的引用"
"通常放在括号里，所以 man:chmod[1] 指的是用户命令，而 man:chmod[2] 指的是系统调"
"用。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1843
msgid ""
"If the name of the manual page is unknown, use `man -k` to search for keywords "
"in the manual page descriptions:"
msgstr "如果手册页的名称不详，使用 `man -k` 来搜索手册页描述中的关键词："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1847
#, no-wrap
msgid "% man -k mail\n"
msgstr "% man -k mail\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1851
msgid ""
"This command displays a list of commands that have the keyword \"mail\" in their "
"descriptions.  This is equivalent to using man:apropos[1]."
msgstr ""
"这条命令显示了一个在描述中含有关键字 \"mail\" 的命令列表。这等同于使用"
" man:apropos[1] 。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1853
msgid ""
"To read the descriptions for all of the commands in [.filename]#/usr/sbin#, type:"
msgstr "要阅读 [.filename]#/usr/sbin# 中所有命令的描述，请输入："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1858
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd /usr/sbin\n"
"% man -f * | more\n"
msgstr ""
"% cd /usr/sbin\n"
"% man -f * | more\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1861
msgid "or"
msgstr "或"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1866
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% cd /usr/sbin\n"
"% whatis * |more\n"
msgstr ""
"% cd /usr/sbin\n"
"% whatis * |more\n"

#. type: Title ===
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1869
#, no-wrap
msgid "GNU Info Files"
msgstr "GNU 信息文件"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1874
msgid ""
"FreeBSD includes several applications and utilities produced by the Free "
"Software Foundation (FSF).  In addition to manual pages, these programs may "
"include hypertext documents called `info` files.  These can be viewed using man:"
"info[1] or, if package:editors/emacs[] is installed, the info mode of emacs."
msgstr ""
"FreeBSD 包括由自由软件基金会 (FSF) 制作的一些应用程序和实用程序。除了手册页面之"
"外，这些程序还可能包括称为 `info` 文件的超文本文件。这些文件可以用 man:info[1] "
"查看，如果安装了 package:editors/emacs[] ，则可以用 emacs 的 info 模式。"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1876
msgid "To use man:info[1], type:"
msgstr "要使用 man:info[1]，请输入："

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1880
#, no-wrap
msgid "% info\n"
msgstr "% info\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/zh-cn/books/handbook/basics/_index.adoc:1883
msgid ""
"For a brief introduction, type `h`.  For a quick command reference, type `?`."
msgstr "要想了解简单的介绍，请键入 `h` ；要想快速参考命令，请键入 `?` 。 "
